title: For Sale:  Thick Wool Shirt
postcontent:
For sale are the vintage US Army wool shirts shown. There are two and one was made several decades earlier than the others. Each is a thick wool shirt, thicker than a Pendleton shirt that you can buy today, and was built to allow some customization for size. If it is a bit small, there are seams on the sleeves and I believe the back that one can rip out, then press flat. This has the effect of allowing the shirt to be sized slightly larger. These were issued starting in the 50's. It is size large for men with chest sizes from 41-45. I measure the sleeve length at 33.5", which means it can be lengthened to about 34.5" by ripping out the seam and pressing the fabric flat.    The older shirt lists the pattern date as JAN 1951.  $20 Each
You can pickup downtown or at I-70 and 291 or ship with FedEx Smart Saver or a padded flat rate envelope (ought to be $5 - $7).
